After 1981, La Monnaie ceased to have Ballet masters, but took on choreographers in residence.
{| class="wikitable" |- ! align="center" width=10%" | Years !! align="center" width="30% | Directors !! align="center" width="30%" | Choreographers in residence |- | <center>1981</center> || [[Gérard Mortier]] || [[Maurice Béjart]] / [[Mark Morris (choreographer)|Mark Morris]] |- | <center>1992</center> || [[Bernard Foccroulle]] || [[Anne Teresa De Keersmaeker]]<ref name=pouget /> |}
After 2007, La Monnaie ceased to take on choreographers in residence. Yet, Rosas and [[Anne Teresa De Keersmaeker]] continue to occupy an important part of La Monnaie's dance programme.<ref name=pouget>Pouget, Isabelle (2017), Les Mots de la Monnaie, Brussels: MARDAGA</ref>
